.PP
\fBExample\ \&11.\ \&A Xfrm interface with physical underlying device\&.\fR
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
# /etc/systemd/network/27\-xfrm\&.netdev
[NetDev]
Name=xfrm0
Kind=xfrm

[Xfrm]
InterfaceId=7
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
# /etc/systemd/network/27\-eth0\&.network
[Match]
Name=eth0

[Network]
Xfrm=xfrm0
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.PP
This creates a
"xfrm0"
interface and binds it to the
"eth0"
device\&. This allows hardware based ipsec offloading to the
"eth0"
nic\&. If offloading is not needed, xfrm interfaces can be assigned to the
"lo"
device\&.
